dayton,  is a small town located in the middle of the shenandoah valley two miles south of harrisonburg (one hour south of winchester; 2.5 hours southwest of washington, dc; one hour northwest of charlottesville) on route 42. home to about 1500 people, dayton is served by three family-owned restaurants, two auto-repair establishments, a bank, a convenience store, a print-shop, two museums, one of the world's largest poultry processing plants and a variety of other worthy establishments including the widely popular dayton farmers market.